cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.CE 

This paper discusses the use of deep neural networks for virtual screening, which is a problem in the field of computational chemistry. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) as these fields often use deep neural networks. The paper also discusses the effects of model architectures, regularization methods, and loss functions, which are topics commonly studied in the field of neural networks, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a likely category as well. Finally, the paper evaluates the reliability of the models, which falls under the category of cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
